S3 details for geovctrs_wkb

new_geovctrs_wkb(
  x = list(),
  include_srid = NA,
  dimensions = 3L,
  endian = NA_integer_
)

is_geovctrs_wkb(x)

validate_geovctrs_wkb(x)

# S3 method for geovctrs_wkb
vec_cast(x, to, ...)

# S3 method for geovctrs_wkb
vec_ptype2(x, y, ...)

Arguments

x

A list() of raw() objects, each of which represent well-known binary
include_srid

Use TRUE to always include, FALSE to never include, or NA to only include if the SRID is non-zero.
dimensions

The maximum number of dimensions to consider when generating text.
endian

Use 0 for big endian, 1 for little endian or NA to use the default on your system.
to

A prototype to cast to. See vctrs::vec_cast() and vctrs::vec_ptype2()
...

Unused
y

A prototype to cast to. See vctrs::vec_cast() and vctrs::vec_ptype2()

Examples

wkb_raw <- as.raw(
  c(
    0x01, 0x01, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00,
    0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x3e, 0x40, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00,
    0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x24, 0x40
  )
)
wkb <- geo_wkb(list(wkb_raw))
is_geovctrs_wkb(wkb)
#> [1] TRUE

# to skip parse validation if you know your object is
# valid, use new_geovctrs_wkb()
new_geovctrs_wkb(list(wkb_raw))
#> <geovctrs_wkb[1]>
#> [1] <POINT (30 10)>
